&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;*This position is available for candidates based in Eastern Europe who are authorized to work in their country of residence. This role will be prospecting the EU Market, and so will be working BST (British Standard Time)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Insight Assurance is a global audit firm on a mission to transform how organizations achieve cybersecurity and compliance. Founded by former Big 4 (EY) professionals, we deliver next-generation audit services across SOC 2, ISO 27001, PCI DSS (QSA), HITRUST, CMMC (C3PAO), and FedRAMP (3PAO) frameworks. We&#39;re not your traditional audit firm — we&#39;re tech-enabled, leveraging compliance automation and advanced collaboration tools to make audits faster, smarter, and more impactful for our clients. Recognized on the Inc. 5000 and Fast 50 lists, Insight Assurance is one of the fastest-growing global audit firms, with 170+ professionals supporting nearly 2,000 clients across the Americas, EMEA, and APAC. If you&#39;re a driven sales professional who thrives on building relationships, driving growth, and being part of a high-performance global team, this is your opportunity to sell trust, innovation, and impact with one of the most exciting firms in the audit industry.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;JOB DESCRIPTION:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Business Development Representative, you will be responsible for identifying, qualifying, and generating new sales leads to support the growth of our company. You will work closely with the sales and marketing teams to develop and execute strategies to expand our customer base and meet revenue targets. This is a remote role based in Eastern Europe. The ideal candidate will have excellent communication skills, the ability to work independently, and a strong desire to succeed in a fast-paced, dynamic environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;KEY RESPONSIBILITIES:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;page-1&quot; class=&quot;_kqswh2mm _bfhku67f _18u01wug _2hwx1wug&quot; data-testid=&quot;page-0&quot;&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and qualify potential new customers through various channels, including cold calling, email campaigns, and social media outreach.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain relationships with potential and existing customers to promote our products and services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with the sales team to develop and execute strategies to increase sales and revenue.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct market research to identify new opportunities and stay up-to-date with industry trends.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with the Growth and Expansion team to develop and implement lead generation campaigns.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate records of all sales and customer interactions in our CRM system.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attend trade shows, conferences, and other industry events to promote our products and services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;REQUIREMENTS:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;4+ years of experience in sales, marketing, or a similar role.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree in business, marketing, or a related field preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record of generating leads and meeting sales targets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with CRM systems and sales tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and presentation skills, with fluency in English (additional European languages a plus).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong organizational and multitasking abilities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work independently and as part of a globally distributed team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be experienced in B2B, preferably in SMB and Mid-Market, with a proven track record.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have entrepreneurial spirit, initiative, and autonomy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must be based in Eastern Europe and authorize

